project.name: cmi5.js
project.description: JavaScript implementation of cmi5 AU runtime

Cmi5.name: Cmi5
Cmi5.description:
Top level interface constructor.

It is highly recommended to use asynchronous calls to methods supporting a callback.

params.name: launchString
params.description: AU Launch URL providing configuration options

throws.description: Invalid launch string

classitems.description: Version of this library
classitems.name: VERSION

classitems.description: Whether or not to enable debug logging
classitems.name: DEBUG

classitems.description:
Method to call to start the AU runtime

This is a simplified "boot" sequence for the AU that will call the individual parts of the start up sequence that would otherwise need to be called in order sequentially.
classitems.name: start

params.name: callback
params.description: Function to call on error or success

params.name: events
params.description: Functions to run at specific execution points

props.name: postFetch
props.description: Function to run after retrieving fetchUrl result

props.name: launchData
props.description: Function to run after retrieving launch data

props.name: learnerPrefs
props.description: Function to run after retrieving learner preferences

props.name: initializeStatement
props.description: Function to run after saving initialization statement

classitems.description:
Method to POST to the fetchUrl to retrieve the LRS credentials

`setFetch` has to be called first and is called by the constructor if the launch string was provided to it.
classitems.name: postFetch

params.name: callback
params.description: Function to call on error or success

classitems.description:
Method to load the LMS.LaunchData state document populated by the LMS

Fetch data has to have already been loaded, in order to have LRS credential.
classitems.name: loadLMSLaunchData

params.name: callback
params.description: Function to call on error or success

classitems.description: Method to load learner prefs agent profile document possibly populated by the LMS
classitems.name: loadLearnerPrefs

params.name: callback
params.description: Function to call on error or success

classitems.description: Method to save learner prefs to agent profile document in LRS
classitems.name: saveLearnerPrefs

params.name: callback
params.description: Function to call on error or success

classitems.description: Finalize initialization process by sending initialized statement, starting duration tracker, and marking AU active
classitems.name: initialize

params.name: callback
params.description: Function to call on error or success

throws.description:
• Learner prefs not loaded
  • AU already initialized

classitems.description: Method to indicate session termination should occur, sends terminated statement, marks AU inactive
classitems.name: terminate

params.name: callback
params.description: Function to call on error or success

throws.description:
• AU not initialized
  • AU already terminated

classitems.description: Method to indicate learner has completed the AU, sends completed statement
classitems.name: completed

params.name: callback
params.description: Function to call on error or success

throws.description:
• AU not active
  • AU not in normal launch mode
  • AU already completed

classitems.description: Method to indicate learner has passed the AU, sends passed statement with optional score
classitems.name: passed

params.name: score
params.description: Score to be included in statement (see `passedStatement`)

params.name: callback
params.description: Function to call on error or success

throws.description:
• AU not active,
  • AU not in normal launch mode,
  • AU already passed,
  • Failed to create passed statement (usually because of malformed score)

classitems.description: Method to indicate learner has failed the AU, sends failed statement with optional score
classitems.name: failed

params.name: score
params.description: Score to be included in statement (see `failedStatement`)

params.name: callback
params.description: Function to call on error or success

throws.description:
• AU not active
  • AU not in normal launch mode
  • AU already passed/failed
  • Failed to create failed statement (usually because of malformed score)

classitems.description: Method indicating whether the AU is currently active, has been initialized and not terminated
classitems.name: isActive

classitems.description:
Safe version of logging, only displays when .DEBUG is true, and console.log
is available

See `console.log` for parameters.
classitems.name: log

classitems.description:
Switch on/off whether a source activity is included in statements by default

Default: on
classitems.name: includeSourceActivity

params.name: val
params.description: true is include, false is exclude

classitems.description:
Initialize the LRS to a `TinCan.LRS` object or update the existing object which will be used for all xAPI communications

Called by the `Cmi5` constructor when provided a launch URL.

params.name: endpoint
params.description: LRS location

params.description: Authentication token value

classitems.description:
Initialize the actor using a `TinCan.Agent` that will represent the learner

Called by the `Cmi5` constructor when provided a launch URL.

Set the registration value

classitems.description: Validate a Score object's properties
classitems.name: validateScore

params.name: score
params.description: Score object to validate

throws.description:
• Null or missing score argument
  • Non-integer min or max value (when provided)
  • Non-number, negative, or greater than 1 scaled value (when provided)
  • Non-integer, missing or invalid min/max, raw value (when provided)

return.description: true for passing, otherwise exception is thrown

classitems.description:
Prepare a cmi5 "allowed" statement including the actor, verb, object, and context

Used to construct a cmi5 "allowed" statement with all relevant information that can then be optionally added to prior to sending.
classitems.name: prepareStatement

params.name: verbId
params.description: Verb identifier combined with other cmi5 pre-determined information (must be IRI)

classitems.description: Store provided statement in the configured LRS
classitems.name: sendStatement

params.name: st
params.description: Statement to be stored

params.name: callback
params.description: Function to run on success/failure of statement save

classitems.description:
Advanced Usage: retrieve prepared "initialized" statement

Statement methods are provided for users that want to implement
a queueing like mechansim or something similar where they are expected
to abide by the AU restrictions on what statements can be sent, etc. on
their own.
classitems.name: initializedStatement

classitems.description:
Advanced Usage: retrieve prepared "terminated" statement

Statement methods are provided for users that want to implement
a queueing like mechansim or something similar where they are expected
to abide by the AU restrictions on what statements can be sent, etc. on
their own.
classitems.name: terminatedStatement

classitems.description:
Advanced Usage: retrieve prepared "passed" statement

Statement methods are provided for users that want to implement
a queueing like mechansim or something similar where they are expected
to abide by the AU restrictions on what statements can be sent, etc. on
their own.
classitems.name: passedStatement

params.name: score
params.description: Object to be used as the score, must meet masteryScore requirements, etc.

classitems.description:
